This paper focuses on improving the performance of the RPL routing protocol for Low power Lossy Networks (LLNs) in the context of the Internet of Things (IoT). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms to support time-varying data traffic loads and node mobility, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The evaluation of the proposed approach involves real-world experiments and large-scale simulations, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
